# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

Add a new fictional **PulseBoard** channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary
real-time bulletin board platform where users post to named "boards" (group chats, prefixed
with `#`) and send direct messages to individual users. It must support `chatTypes:
["direct", "group"]` with a 4000-character text chunk limit.

All files are **new** — only created under `extensions/pulseboard/`. No existing files are
modified (the `extensions/*` glob in `pnpm-workspace.yaml` auto-discovers the new package).

Reference plugins studied: **Nostr** (minimal DM-only, good baseline), **IRC** (DM + group
with setup wizard), **Mattermost** (full group/DM with `attachedResults` outbound).

---

## Invariant Compliance

The test at `src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts` enforces four rules that must align:

| Rule | Value |
|------|-------|
| Directory name | `pulseboard` |
| `openclaw.plugin.json` `id` | `pulseboard` |
| `package.json` `name` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` |
| `package.json` `openclaw.channel.id` | `pulseboard` |
| `package.json` `openclaw.install.npmSpec` | `@openclaw/pulseboard` |

---

## Files to Create

### `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`
Plugin manifest. Required by the plugin loader.

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`
npm package metadata with OpenClaw channel registration.

Key fields:
- `"name": "@openclaw/pulseboard"`
- `"version": "2026.4.1-beta.1"` (aligned with current release cycle)
- `"type": "module"`
- `openclaw.extensions: ["./index.ts"]`
- `openclaw.setupEntry: "./setup-entry.ts"`
- `openclaw.channel.id: "pulseboard"`, `.label: "PulseBoard"`, `.selectionLabel: "PulseBoard (Bulletin Board)"`, `.detailLabel: "PulseBoard"`, `.docsPath: "/channels/pulseboard"`, `.docsLabel: "pulseboard"`, `.blurb: "real-time bulletin board with named boards and direct messages."`
- `openclaw.install.npmSpec: "@openclaw/pulseboard"`
- `devDependencies: { "openclaw": "workspace:*" }`
- `peerDependencies: { "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1" }` with `peerDependenciesMeta.openclaw.optional: true`

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts`
Main entry point via `defineChannelPluginEntry` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`.

```ts
import type { ChannelPlugin } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { defineChannelPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
import { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export { setPulseBoardRuntime } from "./src/runtime.js";

export default defineChannelPluginEntry({
  id: "pulseboard",
  name: "PulseBoard",
  description: "PulseBoard bulletin board channel plugin",
  plugin: pulseBoardPlugin as ChannelPlugin,
  setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime,
});
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts`
Setup-mode entry point (used by `openclaw setup`).

```ts
import { defineSetupPluginEntry } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
import { pulseBoardPlugin } from "./src/channel.js";
export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin);
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/api.ts`
Public barrel — exposed to core/tests per boundary rules.

```ts
export * from "./src/accounts.js";
export * from "./src/setup-surface.js";
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/runtime-api.ts`
Thin runtime barrel (matches project convention for bundled plugins).

```ts
// Private runtime barrel for the bundled PulseBoard extension.
export type { PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`
Config type definitions (plain TypeScript) and Zod runtime schema.

**Plain types:**
```ts
// Per-board overrides
type PulseBoardBoardConfig = {
  enabled?: boolean;
  requireMention?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// Account-level configuration (mirrors channels.pulseboard.*)
type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  apiToken?: string | SecretInput;        // from buildSecretInputSchema()
  username?: string;
  serverUrl?: string;                     // e.g. "https://api.pulseboard.io"
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardBoardConfig>;
  defaultBoard?: string;
  textChunkLimit?: number;
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
};

// Top-level config (supports optional multi-account)
type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// Extended OpenClaw config
type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

// Fully resolved, normalized account (no undefined credentials)
type ResolvedPulseBoardAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  name?: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  configured: boolean;    // true iff apiToken && username are non-empty
  apiToken: string;
  username: string;
  serverUrl: string;
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
};
```

**Zod schema (`PulseBoardConfigSchema`):** uses primitives from
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-primitives`:
- `apiToken`: `buildSecretInputSchema().optional()`
- `dmPolicy`: `DmPolicySchema.optional()`
- `allowFrom`: `AllowFromListSchema`
- `markdown`: `MarkdownConfigSchema`

Export both `PulseBoardConfigSchema` (Zod) and `pulseBoardChannelConfigSchema`
(JSON Schema via `buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema)`).

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`
Account resolution — core of config wiring.

**Exports:**
- `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID = "default"` (constant)
- `resolvePulseBoardAccountIds(cfg: OpenClawConfig): string[]`  
  Returns keys from `cfg.channels?.pulseboard?.accounts` ∪ `[DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID]`
- `resolvePulseBoardAccount(cfg: OpenClawConfig, accountId?: string | null): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`  
  Merges top-level config with per-account overrides; reads `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN` env var
  as fallback for `apiToken`; sets `configured: !!(resolvedToken && resolvedUsername)`;
  defaults `serverUrl` to `"https://api.pulseboard.io"`

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`
Runtime slot using `createPluginRuntimeStore` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store`.

```ts
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };
```

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/send.ts`
Simulated message sending (PulseBoard is fictional; uses `fetch`-style stub).

**Export:**
```ts
export async function sendPulseBoardMessage(
  to: string,
  text: string,
  opts: { cfg: OpenClawConfig; accountId?: string; replyTo?: string | null },
): Promise<{ messageId: string }>
```

Logic:
- Calls `resolvePulseBoardAccount(cfg, accountId)` — throws if not configured
- Determines destination type: `to.startsWith("#")` → board post; else → DM
- In real usage would POST to `account.serverUrl/api/boards/<board>/messages` or
  `account.serverUrl/api/dms/<user>` with bearer auth; since fictional, returns
  a deterministic stub `messageId` (e.g. `pb_${Date.now()}`)
- Accepts `replyTo` for threaded replies (passes as `replyToId` in request body)

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/setup-surface.ts`
Interactive setup wizard + CLI adapter.

**`pulseBoardSetupAdapter`** (`ChannelSetupAdapter`):
- `resolveAccountId: () => DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`
- `applyAccountName`: patches `channels.pulseboard.name`
- `validateInput`: requires `apiToken` or `useEnv`; validates `serverUrl` is https if provided

**`pulseBoardSetupWizard`** (`ChannelSetupWizard`):
- `channel: "pulseboard"`
- `status`: `createStandardChannelSetupStatus` — configured when `apiToken + username` present
- `introNote`: title "PulseBoard setup", explains getting an API token from PulseBoard
- `envShortcut`: checks for `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN` env var
- `credentials`:
  - `inputKey: "apiToken"`, `preferredEnvVar: "PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN"`,
    `inputPrompt: "PulseBoard API token"`, `keepPrompt: "API token already set. Keep it?"`
- `textInputs`:
  - `inputKey: "username"` — PulseBoard handle, required
  - `inputKey: "serverUrl"` — defaults to `https://api.pulseboard.io`, optional
- `groupAccess`:
  - `label: "PulseBoard boards"`, `placeholder: "#announcements, #dev, *"`
  - policy/allowlist wiring for group access
- `allowFrom`: DM allowlist (username-based)
- `dmPolicy`: standard DM policy step
- `disable`: patches `{ enabled: false }` into config

---

### `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts`
Main plugin object — the heart of the extension.

Uses `createChatChannelPlugin` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`.  
Imports `chunkTextForOutbound` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/text-chunking`.  
Imports status helpers from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` and
`openclaw/plugin-sdk/extension-shared`.

**Structure:**

```
createChatChannelPlugin({
  base: {
    id: "pulseboard",
    meta: {
      id: "pulseboard",
      label: "PulseBoard",
      selectionLabel: "PulseBoard (Bulletin Board)",
      detailLabel: "PulseBoard",
      docsPath: "/channels/pulseboard",
      docsLabel: "pulseboard",
      blurb: "real-time bulletin board with named boards and direct messages.",
      quickstartAllowFrom: true,
    },
    capabilities: {
      chatTypes: ["direct", "group"],
      media: false,
      blockStreaming: false,
    },
    reload: { configPrefixes: ["channels.pulseboard"] },
    configSchema: pulseBoardChannelConfigSchema,
    setup: pulseBoardSetupAdapter,
    setupWizard: pulseBoardSetupWizard,
    config: {
      listAccountIds: (cfg) => resolvePulseBoardAccountIds(cfg),
      resolveAccount: (cfg, accountId) => resolvePulseBoardAccount(cfg, accountId),
      isConfigured: (account) => account.configured,
      describeAccount: (account) => ({
        accountId: account.accountId,
        name: account.name,
        enabled: account.enabled,
        configured: account.configured,
      }),
    },
    groups: {
      resolveRequireMention: ({ cfg, accountId, groupId }) => {
        const account = resolvePulseBoardAccount(cfg, accountId);
        return account.config.boards?.[groupId]?.requireMention ?? false;
      },
    },
    messaging: {
      normalizeTarget: (target) => {
        const t = target.trim();
        // Keep # prefix for boards, lowercase both
        return t.startsWith("#") ? t.toLowerCase() : t.toLowerCase();
      },
      targetResolver: {
        looksLikeId: (input) => /^#?\w+/.test(input.trim()),
        hint: "<#board|username>",
      },
    },
    status: createComputedAccountStatusAdapter<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>({
      defaultRuntime: createDefaultChannelRuntimeState(DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID),
      buildChannelSummary: ({ snapshot }) =>
        buildPassiveChannelStatusSummary(snapshot, { channel: "pulseboard" }),
      resolveAccountSnapshot: ({ account }) => ({
        configured: account.configured,
        running: false,
      }),
    }),
    gateway: {
      startAccount: async (ctx) => {
        // Simulated: a real impl would open a WebSocket to ctx.account.serverUrl
        // and call dispatchInbound* helpers on inbound messages.
        ctx.log?.info(`[pulseboard:${ctx.account.accountId}] gateway started`);
        return { stop: () => {
          ctx.log?.info(`[pulseboard:${ctx.account.accountId}] gateway stopped`);
        }};
      },
    },
  },
  pairing: {
    text: {
      idLabel: "pulseBoardUser",
      message: "Your PulseBoard pairing request has been approved.",
      normalizeAllowEntry: (entry) => entry.trim().toLowerCase(),
      notify: async ({ cfg, id, message, accountId }) => {
        await sendPulseBoardMessage(id, message, { cfg, accountId: accountId ?? undefined });
      },
    },
  },
  security: {
    dm: {
      channelKey: "pulseboard",
      resolvePolicy: (account) => account.config.dmPolicy,
      resolveAllowFrom: (account) => account.config.allowFrom,
      policyPathSuffix: "dmPolicy",
      normalizeEntry: (raw) => raw.trim().toLowerCase(),
    },
  },
  outbound: {
    base: {
      deliveryMode: "direct",
      chunker: chunkTextForOutbound,
      chunkerMode: "markdown",
      textChunkLimit: 4000,
    },
    attachedResults: {
      channel: "pulseboard",
      sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendPulseBoardMessage(to, text, {
          cfg, accountId: accountId ?? undefined, replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
        }),
      sendMedia: async ({ cfg, to, text, mediaUrl, accountId, replyToId }) =>
        sendPulseBoardMessage(to, mediaUrl ? `${text}\n${mediaUrl}` : text, {
          cfg, accountId: accountId ?? undefined, replyTo: replyToId ?? undefined,
        }),
    },
  },
})
```

---

