**`pulseBoardSetupWizard`** (`ChannelSetupWizard`):
- `channel: "pulseboard"`
- `status`: `createStandardChannelSetupStatus` — configured when `apiToken + username` present
- `introNote`: title "PulseBoard setup", explains getting an API token from PulseBoard
- `envShortcut`: checks for `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN` env var
- `credentials`:
  - `inputKey: "apiToken"`, `preferredEnvVar: "PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN"`,
    `inputPrompt: "PulseBoard API token"`, `keepPrompt: "API token already set. Keep it?"`
- `textInputs`:
  - `inputKey: "username"` — PulseBoard handle, required
  - `inputKey: "serverUrl"` — defaults to `https://api.pulseboard.io`, optional
- `groupAccess`:
  - `label: "PulseBoard boards"`, `placeholder: "#announcements, #dev, *"`
  - policy/allowlist wiring for group access
- `allowFrom`: DM allowlist (username-based)
- `dmPolicy`: standard DM policy step
- `disable`: patches `{ enabled: false }` into config

